item.title: What if my Missouri due date falls before the federal due date?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: You must file and pay an estimated return by the original Missouri due date and when the federal return is completed, file an amended Missouri return.

item.title: Does Missouri require depreciation to be added back?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: No. The provision requiring the adding back of bonus depreciation includes property purchased on or after July 1, 2002 but before July 1, 2003, in determining if the bonus depreciation must be used as a Missouri modification. Property purchased before July 1, 2002 and after June 30, 2003, does not qualify for the modification.

item.title: Where can I get my corporate kit or corporate seal?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Corporate kits may be purchased from a legal stationery store. A corporate kit usually contains a corporate seal, blank stock certificates and forms for the adoption of by-laws and recording the minutes of meetings. Rather than composing their own forms, some may find it easier to use the preprinted forms provided in a corporate kit. Please note that New York State law does not require a corporation to have a seal. Your telephone book’s yellow pages or a yellow pages information operator (your area code + 555-1212) may be helpful in locating a legal stationery store.

item.title: How do I determine the county average wage or the state average wage?
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The county average wage and statewide average wage is calculated by the Department of Economic Development and can be found at www.missourieconomy.org/indicators/countywage.stm. The statewide average wage is listed last on the table.
